## Description

Would the team be open to having example of `auth.json` in the `skopeo` documentation? Unless I missed it, I did not see any reference to the structure of `auth.json`. I resorted to dissecting my `.docker/config.json`. I know these .json files are typically generated via `podman login` or `docker login` but in the cases were you'd just like to only have `skopeo` installed to minimize dependencies it'd be good to give an example and snippet of how to generate a basic `auth.json`.

It could be as simple as:
```
$ echo -n 'sarcasticadmin:mysupersecretpassword' | base64
c2FyY2FzdGljYWRtaW46bXlzdXBlcnNlY3JldHBhc3N3b3Jk

$ cat << EOF > auth.json
{
        "auths": {
                "https://index.docker.io/v1/": {
                        "auth": "c2FyY2FzdGljYWRtaW46bXlzdXBlcnNlY3JldHBhc3N3b3Jk"
                }
        }
}
EOF
```

