@mtrmac The docker source seems to have the same problem with not telling the user what `config.json` (similar to `auth.json`) actually contains, its just snippets of things like `credsStore` and `credHelpers` options but not a complete `config.json` example.

@TomSweeneyRedHat thank you, the manpage in [containers/image](https://github.com/containers/image/blob/fe9e1741e53189457e49f8014b8d4c79f4fc32fe/docs/containers-auth.json.5.md) is exactly what I was looking for! Do you think it'd be beneficial to put in the base64 one-liner of username, colon, password in the `Format` section of `containers-auth.json`?

Once #865 finishes: Would it be beneficial to have `skopeo-login` `manpage`  reference `containers-auth.json` in its `Also see` section? Otherwise its seems like `containers-auth.json` would be hard to find
